Rating: 4
Delicious! Thought I had parchment paper but discovered I was out so I used an All Clad double griddle that has a very dark non-stick surface. I pre-heated the oven to 490, put the dough in for about 5 minutes, took it out, laid the mushrooms in a single layer, sprinkled TBSP of kosher salt and some pepper, laid the cheese and cooked for 10 minutes. It came out perfect. I almost sauteed the mushrooms but glad I didn't as they were well cooked from the high heat. The crust was very crisp - about 1 minute from burning. I'm indifferent on the truffle oil. I like truffle oil but I think this would be fine with or without and my wife agreed. Found the Taleggio cheese at Whole Foods and it was very tasty. Next time I might do some sweet onions and skip the truffle oil. All in all a great recipe.

